commit.message:
Raise AugeasRuntimeError in newer APIs (#52)

Instead of raising RuntimeError when an augeas API fails, use the
AugeasRuntimeError subclass so all the details of the augeas error are
available to users.

Applies 927a25c0729dc88246b44f1b4911c8034ea32cb4 to the newer APIs
introduced with commits dca8493535edd5ae6de788ed9a86c6c05f26fd3f and
6cecd44f5c2e91451d5357880187536bbe045903. This also removes the
printing of the error code when only 0/1 are possible values, and
fixes the mentioned API in one message.

commit.message:
Use CFFI in out-of-line API mode (#49)

Currently, ffi.py is called during setup to generate augeas.py; this
file would normally be used for out-of-line ABI mode. ffi.py is also
imported at run-time, instead of the generated augeas.py, and used in
in-line ABI mode.

This changes usage of CFFI to out-of-line API mode (CFFI's "main mode of
usage"): ffi.py is called during setup to generate _augeas.abi3.so (a C
extension module); this generated module is imported at run-time.

With this change, the headers/development files for augeas (i.e.
libaugeas-dev on Debian, augeas-devel on Fedora, etc.) and the C
compiler are required for build/setup. (These were not necessary
previously.)

Closes https://github.com/hercules-team/python-augeas/issues/48.

commit.message:
Fix the LGPL license text & address (#44)

* Update LGPL 2.1 license text

Sync it from the canonical location:
https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.1.txt

* Update FSF postal address

Taken from the current LGPL 2.1 license text.

Fixes #43.

Fix the majority of PEP8 issues (#41)

* pep8: fix whitespaces in lines

Add or remove whitespaces within lines, adapting the indentation if
needed.  This fixes the following issues:
E124, E201, E202, E211, E221, E231, and E251.

This commit is best viewed with 'git diff -w'.

* pep8: add missing empty lines

This fixes the following issue: E302.

* pep8: fix comparisons with None

Use 'foo is not None' to compare against None.

This fixes the following issues: E711, and E721.

* pep8: wrap lines longer than 80 characters

This fixes the following issue: E501.

* pep8: fix location of imports in Augeas

Move them before other instructions, as recommended.
This fixes the following issue: E402, but not in test_augeas (which
needs to augment sys.path, in case it is run as standalone script).

test: switch away from deprecated params

Do not pass the 'name' parameter to add_transform.

test: make 'setup.py test' work

- add an empty __init__.py in 'test', so the whole directory is
  recognized as module
- tell setuptools how to find the test suite
- adapt the own Makefile to use 'setup.py test', getting rid of the
  Makefile in 'test', as no more needed

test: fix discovery of location

Use __file__ to detect the location of the script instead of sys.argv,
so it will work also when loaded as module.

test: use more modern unittest API

Considering that Python >= 2.7 is required, make use of non-deprecated
APIs of the unittest module for the checks:
- use the better APIs where available
- use assertRaises instead of manual exception checking

commit.message:
Refactor exceptions from Augeas errors

Right now, when an augeas function returns an error, a generic Python
exception (IOError, RuntimeError, or ValueError) is raised, with no way
to even known the details of the failure.

Revamp a bit the system:
- create subclasses of exceptions based on the existing exception
  thrown, to maintain compatibility with existing users; these new
  exceptions have extra members 'error' (for the error code), 'msg'
  (for the error message), 'minor' (for the error explanations), and
  'details' (for the details)
- add AUG_* constants for the all the Augeas errors
- simplify the own error strings to mention just the function, since
  the exception message will contain all the available details
- turn the AUG_ENOMEM error into a Python MemoryError exception, more
  Pythonic

Fixes #8.

Add a simple Sphinx-based API doc

Mostly generated from the docstrings, using a basic index.

Rework docstring comments in preparation for sphinx

Polish the docstring comments, so they will play more nicely with
Sphinx:
- place opening, and closing """ in own lines, so they will not be
  part of changed lines anymore
- borrow from the C augeas the docs for the open flags
- apply sphinx markup all around, e.g. for references, preformatted
  text, few parameters, etc
- make sure to not exceed 80 columns, in line with PEP 8
- miscellaneous fixes

setup.py: isolate name and version as variables

This way they can be used also for other parameters.

Add helper _optffistring()

Factorize this small code, which is repeated 3 times already, and will
be used further.
Remove unused variables
Remove ununsed imports
